This paper discusses the use of evolutionary processes to develop new network topologies for deep neural networks. This topic is most closely related to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), which is the most likely category for this paper. The paper also discusses the use of fitness prediction techniques, which is related to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of large datasets, which is related to the sub-category of Computer Vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the feasibility of using subsets obtained in an evolutionary process to estimate the fitness of the network topology, which is related to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
